  "explanation": "Dynamic programming or two pointers with greedy star matching.",
  "answer": "def isMatch(s, p):\n    m, n = len(s), len(p); i, j, si, star = 0, 0, -1, -1\n    while i < m:\n        if j < n and (p[j] == '?' or p[j] == s[i]): i += 1; j += 1\n        elif j < n and p[j] == '*': star = j; j += 1; si = i\n        elif star != -1: j = star + 1; si += 1; i = si\n        else: return False\n    while j < n and p[j] == '*': j += 1\n    return j == n",
